IRowPosition Interface

In this Article

Provides an implementation of the OLE DB IRowPosition interface for use by applications upgraded from Visual Basic 6.0.

Syntax

Declaration

[System.Obsolete("Microsoft.VisualBasic.Compatibility.* classes are obsolete and supported within 32 bit processes only. http://go.microsoft.com/fwlink/?linkid=160862")]
[System.Runtime.InteropServices.Guid("0C733A94-2A1C-11CE-ADE5-00AA0044773D")]
[System.Runtime.InteropServices.InterfaceType(System.Runtime.InteropServices.ComInterfaceType.InterfaceIsIUnknown)]
public interface IRowPosition

Remarks

Note

Functions and objects in the N:Microsoft.VisualBasic.Compatibility.VB6?qualifyHint=False&autoUpgrade=True namespace are provided for use by the tools for upgrading from Visual Basic 6.0 to Visual Basic 2008. In most cases, these functions and objects duplicate functionality that you can find in other namespaces in the .NET Framework. They are necessary only when the Visual Basic 6.0 code model differs significantly from the .NET Framework implementation.

Methods summary

ClearRowPosition()

Clears the row position.
GetRowPosition(Int32,Int32,Int32)

Retrieves the current row position.
GetRowset(Guid,Object)

Returns the current underlying Rowset.
Initialize(Object)

Initializes the row position object by setting the source rowset.
SetRowPosition(Int32,Int32,Int32)

Sets the current row position.

  • GetRowPosition(Int32,Int32,Int32)

    Retrieves the current row position.

    public void GetRowPosition (out int hChapter, out int hRow, out int dbPositionFlags);

    Parameters

    • hChapter
      Int32

      A pointer to memory in which to return the chapter associated with the current row. If the rowset is not chaptered, hChapter is set to DB_NULL_HCHAPTER. If hChapter is a null pointer on input, no chapter value is returned.

    • hRow
      Int32

      A pointer to memory in which to return the hRow of the current row position; or DB_NULL_HROW if there is no current row position.

    • dbPositionFlags
      Int32

      A pointer to memory in which to return additional information about the row position.

    Remarks

    Note

    Functions and objects in the N:Microsoft.VisualBasic.Compatibility.VB6?qualifyHint=False&autoUpgrade=True namespace are provided for use by the tools for upgrading from Visual Basic 6.0 to Visual Basic 2008. In most cases, these functions and objects duplicate functionality that you can find in other namespaces in the .NET Framework. They are necessary only when the Visual Basic 6.0 code model differs significantly from the .NET Framework implementation.

  • GetRowset(Guid,Object)

    Returns the current underlying Rowset.

    public void GetRowset (ref Guid iid, out object rowset);

    Parameters

    • iid
      Guid

      The requested IID for the rowset returned in rowset.

    • rowset
      Object

      A pointer to memory in which to return the interface pointer of the underlying rowset.

    Remarks

In most cases, these functions and objects duplicate functionality that you can find in other namespaces in the .NET Framework. They are necessary only when the Visual Basic 6.0 code model differs significantly from the .NET Framework implementation.

    Initializes the row position object by setting the source rowset.

    Parameters

    • rowset

      Pointer to an interface on the source rowset.

In most cases, these functions and objects duplicate functionality that you can find in other namespaces in the .NET Framework. They are necessary only when the Visual Basic 6.0 code model differs significantly from the .NET Framework implementation.

  • SetRowPosition(Int32,Int32,Int32)

    Sets the current row position.

    public void SetRowPosition (int hChapter, int hRow, int dbPositionFlags);

    Parameters

    • hChapter
      Int32

      The chapter associated with the current row, or with DB_NULL_HCHAPTER if the rowset is not chaptered.

    • hRow
      Int32

      The new current row.

    • dbPositionFlags
      Int32

      A flag indicating additional information about the new row position.
